## 6. Skeleton components réutilisables

Dans `components/ui/skeletons/`. Un skeleton = une forme dédiée, pas un générique.

```tsx
// components/ui/skeletons/SkeletonCard.tsx
export function SkeletonCard() {
  return (
    <div className="rounded-xl border p-4">
      <div className="h-40 w-full animate-pulse rounded-md bg-gray-200" />
      <div className="mt-4 h-5 w-3/4 animate-pulse rounded bg-gray-200" />
      <div className="mt-2 h-4 w-full animate-pulse rounded bg-gray-200" />
      <div className="mt-2 h-4 w-5/6 animate-pulse rounded bg-gray-200" />
    </div>
  );
}

// components/ui/skeletons/SkeletonTable.tsx
export function SkeletonTable({ rows = 5 }: { rows?: number }) {
  return (
    <div className="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border">
      <div className="border-b bg-gray-50 p-3">
        <div className="h-4 w-40 animate-pulse rounded bg-gray-200" />
      </div>
      {Array.from({ length: rows }).map((_, i) => (
        <div key={i} className="flex gap-4 border-b p-3 last:border-b-0">
          <div className="h-4 flex-1 animate-pulse rounded bg-gray-200" />
          <div className="h-4 w-24 animate-pulse rounded bg-gray-200" />
          <div className="h-4 w-20 animate-pulse rounded bg-gray-200" />
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

// components/ui/skeletons/SkeletonText.tsx
export function SkeletonText({ lines = 3 }: { lines?: number }) {
  return (
    <div className="space-y-2">
      {Array.from({ length: lines }).map((_, i) => (
        <div
          key={i}
          className="h-4 animate-pulse rounded bg-gray-200"
          style={{ width: `${70 + (i % 3) * 10}%` }}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

Règle : un skeleton par composant réel (pattern **skeleton-generator** Karibloom). `SkeletonCard` reflète la `Card`, `SkeletonPizzaCard` reflète la `PizzaCard`, etc.

